  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but is fading hard on H4 at 44, a 56-point divergence that is the single most important signal in this brief, while CHF accelerates to H4 CSM 100 versus D1 33 and AUD surges to H4 CSM 70 versus D1 31, confirming intraday rotation out of USD and into safe-haven CHF and, counter-intuitively, commodity-linked AUD as copper rises 1.36%. USDCHF is the primary expression given the -0.88 EURUSD-USDCHF correlation confirming CHF broad strength, while AUDUSD and AUDJPY exploit the 0.91 correlation cluster with NZD pairs amplifying any AUD leg higher. US Consumer Sentiment deterioration with a bearish USD news bias reinforces fading USD momentum despite the D1 structural buy regime.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nFed Chair policy statement crosses: USDJPY reacts first given CADJPY +0.66 correlation, a hawkish signal triggers USDJPY long continuation above H4 neutral.\nCopper extends above 6.40: AUDUSD breaks H4 resistance, AUDJPY confirms via 0.91 correlation follow-through.\nUS Consumer Confidence print deteriorates further: USDCAD D1 and H4 strong buy signal fails, CAD short squeeze activates on CADJPY selling.",
